      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like you're saying the urban guy is more likely to fail because of his environment, right? so basically even though he hasn't done anything else, his \"lack of stability\" makes him a bigger threat in the eyes of the law than the suburban guy. wouldn't focusing on \"risk\" like that just lead to harsher sentences for people from those communities just for existing there?",
